# SPLICE Website - Continuation Prompt

## Objective
Build a high-converting signup website for SPLICE at `/Users/imorgado/SPLICE/splice-website` using Next.js + Tailwind + Vercel. Focus heavily on the main landing page with UX psychology principles.

## Key Files
- Backend API: `splice-backend/server.js` (Stripe integration at lines 184-241)
- Pricing tiers: `splice-backend/services/usageTracking.js` (lines 1-50)
- Existing Stripe config: `splice-backend/routes/billing.js`
- CLAUDE.md: Update after completion

## Competitor Analysis - Why SPLICE Wins

| Feature | SPLICE | FireCut ($14-29/mo) | AutoPod ($29/yr) |
|---------|--------|---------------------|------------------|
| AI Music Generation | ✅ Mureka + Scene-Aware | ❌ | ❌ |
| Song Identification | ✅ ACRCloud | ❌ | ❌ |
| Vocal Isolation | ✅ Replicate Demucs | ❌ | ❌ |
| Text-Based Editing | ✅ Full LCS diff | ❌ | ❌ |
| Animated Captions | ✅ 5 templates (MrBeast, Hormozi) | ✅ Basic | ❌ |
| Social Reframe | ✅ Face tracking + safe zones | ❌ | ✅ Basic |
| Multitrack/Multicam | ✅ Auto-balance | ✅ | ✅ |
| Silence Removal | ✅ RMS + Whisper + FFprobe | ✅ | ✅ |
| Take Detection | ✅ GPT-4o-mini | ✅ | ❌ |
| CEP + UXP Support | ✅ Both (PP 14.0-25.9+) | ✅ CEP only | ✅ CEP only |
| Chapter Detection | ✅ AI + YouTube timestamps | ✅ | ❌ |
| Profanity Bleeping | ✅ 5 bleep types + WAV synthesis | ❌ | ❌ |

**Key Differentiators:**
1. **Only plugin with AI music generation** - Create custom background music
2. **Most comprehensive feature set** - 30+ endpoints vs competitors' 5-10
3. **Modern UXP architecture** - Future-proof for Premiere Pro 25.6+
4. **Text-based editing** - Delete text = delete video (unique)

## UX Psychology Principles (Maximize Conversion)

### Cognitive Biases to Leverage:
1. **Anchoring** - Show Pro tier first ($49) to make Starter ($19) seem cheap
2. **Social Proof** - "Join 10,000+ editors" with testimonials
3. **Loss Aversion** - "Stop wasting 10+ hours per video"
4. **Scarcity** - "Limited beta pricing" badge
5. **Authority** - "Powered by OpenAI Whisper, GPT-4o, Mureka AI"
6. **Reciprocity** - Free 14-day trial, no credit card required
7. **Commitment** - Progressive disclosure (email → trial → paid)

### Landing Page Structure (F-Pattern + Z-Pattern Hybrid):
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ HERO: "Edit 10x Faster with AI" + CTA + Video      │
│ ├─ Pain point headline                              │
│ ├─ 3 bullet benefits                                │
│ ├─ Primary CTA: "Start Free Trial"                  │
│ └─ Secondary: "Watch Demo" (reduces friction)       │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ SOCIAL PROOF BAR: Logos + "Trusted by X editors"   │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ PROBLEM/SOLUTION: Before/After comparison          │
│ ├─ "Without SPLICE: 8 hours editing"               │
│ └─ "With SPLICE: 45 minutes"                        │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ FEATURES: 6 cards with micro-animations            │
│ ├─ Silence Removal    ├─ AI Music                  │
│ ├─ Take Detection     ├─ Animated Captions         │
│ ├─ Text Editing       ├─ Social Reframe            │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ COMPETITOR COMPARISON: Side-by-side table          │
│ └─ "Why editors switch from FireCut"               │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ TESTIMONIALS: 3 video creators with photos         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ PRICING: 3 tiers with Pro highlighted              │
│ ├─ Starter: $19/mo (12 hrs)                        │
│ ├─ Pro: $49/mo (30 hrs) ← "Most Popular"           │
│ └─ Team: $149/mo (100 hrs)                         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ FAQ: Accordion with common objections              │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ FINAL CTA: "Ready to edit 10x faster?"             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Design Inspiration (Award-Winning Patterns):
- **Landingfolio**: Clear value props, gradient backgrounds, prominent CTAs
- **Awwwards**: Purposeful animations, hover effects, scroll-triggered reveals
- **One Page Love**: Smooth section transitions, visual hierarchy
- **Checklist.design**: Accessible forms, clear error states, responsive
- **Sidebar.io**: Substance over trends, accessibility-first

### Conversion Optimizations:
1. **Above fold**: Headline + CTA + video visible without scroll
2. **Sticky header**: CTA always accessible
3. **Exit intent popup**: "Wait! Get 20% off your first month"
4. **Chat widget**: Reduce friction for questions
5. **Mobile-first**: 60%+ traffic is mobile
6. **<3s load time**: Optimize images, lazy load

## Pages to Build

1. **`/` (Landing)** - Primary focus, all conversion elements
2. **`/pricing`** - Detailed tier comparison, FAQ
3. **`/download`** - CEP/UXP plugin downloads, installation guide
4. **`/docs`** - Quick start, feature guides
5. **`/api/checkout`** - Stripe checkout session creation
6. **`/api/webhook`** - Stripe webhook handler (reuse from backend)

## Tech Stack
```
Next.js 14 (App Router)
Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
Framer Motion (animations)
Stripe.js (checkout)
Vercel (deployment)
```

## Testing Process (MANDATORY)

After implementing each feature run an end to end test that looks for bottlenecks, bugs, makes sure everything is wired correctly, there are no issues with the UI, the UI and logic are wired correctly, API endpoints are tested and work correctly. the process should work as implement -> end to end test -> identifies a bug -> fixes the bug -> runs the test again -> test comes back clean -> move onto the next feature -> repeat this process until all features are completed. After everything has been completed then it should run an end to end test that looks tests that everything is wired correctly, implemented, there are no issues, etc.

### Test File Structure:
```
splice-website/
├── tests/
│   ├── landing-e2e.test.js      # Hero, features, CTAs, responsive
│   ├── pricing-e2e.test.js      # Tier display, Stripe integration
│   ├── checkout-e2e.test.js     # Payment flow, error handling
│   ├── download-e2e.test.js     # Plugin downloads, links valid
│   ├── accessibility.test.js    # ARIA, keyboard nav, contrast
│   └── final-integration.test.js # Full site verification
```

### E2E Test Checklist Per Feature:
- [ ] UI renders correctly (no console errors)
- [ ] Responsive on mobile/tablet/desktop
- [ ] All links/buttons functional
- [ ] API endpoints return correct responses
- [ ] Stripe checkout flow works
- [ ] Accessibility (ARIA labels, keyboard nav)
- [ ] Performance (<3s load, Core Web Vitals)
- [ ] Cross-browser (Chrome, Safari, Firefox)

## Implementation Order

1. **Project setup** - Next.js + Tailwind + Vercel config
2. **Landing page hero** - Headline, CTA, video embed
